			<description><![CDATA[<p>
JOB ACTIVITIES<br />
Write copy, upload images and input event details to www.goldstar.com.</p>
<p>
SCHEDULE<br />
Approx. 5-20 hours a week. Exact hours TBD in collaboration with the selected candidate. Flexibility is a must as is the ability to work weekends.</p>
<p>
JOB DESCRIPTION<br />
The Copywriter will work from home writing copy and inputting show details into the Goldstar system. This job would be well suited for someone who is great at: writing for the web, using web functionality, doing online research and proofreading (both words and data).</p>
<p>
This position reports to the Editorial Manager and Director and requires the candidate to work according to editorial guidelines and be extremely detail oriented. In addition to writing and editing, this position involves inputting ticket allotments with speed and accuracy. There is a required week of paid in-house training at our office in Pasadena, Calif.</p>
<p>
The person who fills this position will work a few set hours and then be asked to put in additional hours depending on the amount of work we have available. There is some flexibility in the schedule, and specific hours will be set together with the selected candidate.</p>
<p>
Living in the Los Angeles area is not required, but is preferred for ease of in-person meetings and ongoing training.</p>
<p>
PROFESSIONAL AND PERSONAL PROFILE<br />
The successful candidate is likely to be:<br />
Experienced in writing copy for web or print<br />
Able to create copy that appeals to audiences in a fun and helpful manner<br />
Detail-oriented and fast<br />
Able to work in a team environment and communicate efficiently<br />
Highly competent in using web functionality<br />
Skilled in basic photo editing techniques<br />
Able to use very basic HTML for text formatting</p>
<p>
ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS<br />
Available for one week of in-house training</p>
<p>
COMPENSATION<br />
$25/Hour</p>
<p>
WE RECOMMEND<br />
Reviewing Goldstars website and getting to know the business, with a particular emphasis on how events are written-up and displayed.</p>
<p>
<br />
Reading the job description carefully and making sure this is the right fit before applying.<br />
Writing a cover letter that highlights the ways in which you are particularly well-suited to this role.</p>
